-- 2013-01-24T18:27:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-24/hsbc-expands-latin-equity-research-with-boente-2-more-analysts.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  added three
analysts to its Latin American equity research team, according
to an e-mailed statement.  Sandra Boente, who had previously worked at Deutsche Bank
AG, will cover utility and water companies from New York,
according to the statement. Alexandre Falcao will be responsible
for transport and capital goods sectors from Sao Paulo.
Francisco Schumacher, who will be based New York, was named
strategist for the Andean region.  The three analysts will report to Ben Laidler, the head of
research for the Americas. HSBCâ€™s Latin America equity research
team includes 23 analysts, strategists and economists after
these appointments, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
